cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.CR 

This paper focuses on deep learning for partial person re-identification, which involves computer vision and machine learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel deep learning framework, which involves training and optimization techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. Additionally, the paper uses convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and spatial transformer networks (STNs), which are commonly used in multimedia (cs.MM) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research. Finally, the paper discusses the performance of the proposed method in terms of accuracy and compares it with state-of-the-art methods, which is related to cryptography and security (cs.CR).
